This is a copy of the Utopia fonts which Adobe contributed to the X
consortium (contrib/fonts/Utopia in the distribution), arranged for use
with TeX.  Here is the copyright notice:

  Permission to use, reproduce, display and distribute the listed typefaces
  is hereby granted, provided that the Adobe Copyright notice appears in all
  whole and partial copies of the software and that the following trademark
  symbol and attribution appear in all unmodified copies of the software:

        Copyright (c) 1989 Adobe Systems Incorporated
        Utopia (R)
        Utopia is a registered trademark of Adobe Systems Incorporated

I used the `afm2tfm' program which comes with Tom Rokicki's dvips to
convert the AFM files to TFM and VF files.  You can get dvips from
labrea.stanford.edu.

